  "texts": [
    "These methods use probabilistic structure to produce more reliable cleaned data, whereas we focus on calibrating uncertainty in missing-value imputation.",
    "This section formalizes the imputation problem and reviews the details of the imputers evaluated in our study.",
    "A. Imputation Problem and Missingness MechanismsLet X ∈ R n×d be a data matrix with n rows from an unknown distribution P θ and d attributes.",
    "Missingness is represented by a binary mask M ∈ {0, 1} n×d with M ij = 1 if X ij is observed and 0 otherwise.",
    "Using the Hadamard product ⊙ and the all-ones matrix 1 n×d,X obs = X ⊙ M, X mis = X ⊙ (1 n×d -M).We model the joint distribution of data and missingness asP(X, M) = P θ (X) P ϕ (M | X),where P ϕ (M | X) is the missingness mechanism."
